rsion_id":220,"steps":[{"id":1078343,"guid":"9DDEBB902AB111EB9732BB47823B20A1","previous_id":null,"previous_guid":null,"modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"3DBCEA83610F4953B883D037FCB9CC5B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Molecular Assembly of GST Effector Proteins on Glutathione Beads"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"93E8A6B46BE34FF4A50BA30D0125E80F","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Briefly, glutathione beads are mixed with the desired, purified GST-effector protein of desired concentration (Eq. 1), incubated with rotation <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> at <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">, collected by centrifugation, and resuspended in HPSMT buffer to 10,000 beads\/\u03bcL. Beads are prepared fresh for each experiment and kept <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> until use on the same day. It is desirable to use the beads as a limiting reagent. In this way, uniform site occupancy (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">\u03b8 <\/span><span>in Eq. 1) of the GSH sites is assured for each bead preparation. The equilibrium dissociation constant (<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">K<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">d<\/span><span>\u00a0\u223c\u00a080\u00a0nM) [26] measured for GST-GFP is used to estimate the occupancy of GSH sites on beads according to Eq. (1):<\/span><\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><span style = \"\">\u03b8=([GST effector]_{free}\/Kd)\/(1+([GST effector]_{free}\/Kd))<\/span><\/div><br\/><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Site occupancies of ligand-binding sites at saturation are in the range of 1\u20134\u00a0\u00d7\u00a010<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">6 <\/span><span>ligand sites\/bead. Equation (1) can be used to estimate ligand-occupied sites according to the example: 10,000 beads present an upper limit of 4\u00a0\u00d7\u00a010<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">10 <\/span><span>sites or 3.3\u00a0nM in 20\u00a0\u03bcL. Incubating 800\u00a0nM (10\u00d7<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">K<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;vertical-align:sub;\">d<\/span><span>) GST ligand with 10,000 beads is expected to yield an occupancy, <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">\u03b8<\/span><span>, of 0.91 (or 91%).<\/span><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"AA56DF102AB111EB9732BB47823B20A1","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":0,"title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"B088B7A02AB111EB9732BB47823B20A1","order_id":3,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":4,"unit":"\u00b0C","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"C648CD502AB111EB9732BB47823B20A1","order_id":4,"type_id":24,"title":"temperature","source":{"temperature":0,"unit":"On ice","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":1200,"critical":[{"id":2,"title":"Centrifugation","icon":"CentrifugationIcon"},{"id":40,"title":"Overnight Step","icon":"Overnight"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1078344,"guid":"EEB1A6902AB111EB9732BB47823B20A1","previous_id":1078343,"previous_guid":"9DDEBB902AB111EB9732BB47823B20A1","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"D56FC7F10C10497092D08425575957D2","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"3.3 Molecular Assembly of GST Effector Proteins on Glutathione Beads"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"4E891DBE7D3D46259FAF7A14558F5ADB","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">12\u201318\u00a0h before a putative assay of 12 samples for 5 GTPase targets perform the following:<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":1200,"criti